The Operational Technology Lead will be responsible for technology, security, and process guidance for the Tualatin Manufacturing plant. The focus of this role is to support end-users, manage all OT-related manufacturing infrastructure and provide effective OT systems to maintain manufacturing production targets for the facility. They will provide oversight of the Tualatin manufacturing infrastructure (network services, computer systems, file storage services, IoT, Azure Cloud, Industry 4.0, etc.), and define, execute and monitor overall delivery, reliability and performance of the infrastructure and services which directly impact the plant's success. The successful candidate will collaborate and innovate with stakeholders and global team members to develop and implement secure technology solutions in support of the plantâ€™s manufacturing efforts. Provides leadership to junior support staff and guides priorities in day-to-day activities. 
 
Other Job Responsibilities 
 Model Company core values 
 Provides leadership to junior support staff 
 Project Delivery 
 Creative solution implementation including Internet of Things, Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence 
 Work with business partners to determine direction and identify opportunities for automation and process streamline 
 Monitor and report system, network policy and cyber-security related non-compliance to Fab Manager 
 Collaborate with global manufacturing OT peers
 Ensures GIS-approved projects and directives in support of business requirements are implemented in a timely manner, tracks and reports progress as required, and escalates to management when customer expectations cannot be met. 
 Provide management/support of all computer & network equipment in the manufacturing/logistics infrastructure 
 Act as a point of contact for IT services, business needs, and vendor management 
 Monitors performance and makes appropriate tuning changes 
 Utilize approved procedures to ensure that hardware and software are deployed, implemented, and supported per business requirements and aligned to company standards/policies. 
 Utilize GIS Change Control model when applicable to document the overall status of the Manufacturing Fab environment, including Asset Management\Tracking; Align to Corporate Change Control Board and Vendor\Supplier requirements as necessary. 
 Participate in GIS projects to test, pilot and/or implement new hardware and software as necessary in support of Manufacturing Fab activity\requirements. 
 Other duties and functions to be as assigned. 
